  {
    "client_msg_id": "a3bb1cc1-f559-4218-9eef-1ea21efe9f0b",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I think the problem with making programming feel \"cool\" (apart from what Antranig said) is that if it's via a novelty such as voice interaction, the \"coolness\" will soon wear off as people get used to it. Then what are you left with? Hopefully a more efficient interface, but if that's the real target, it should probably be higher priority.",
    "user": "UCGAK10LS",
